usage:	./corewar [-h -v -c] [-dump[32|64] NBR_CYCLES] [[-n ID] NAME.cor] ...

	-h, -help
		Show this message.

	-v, -verbose
		Print detailed information during execution.

	-c, -color
		Enable colored output.	

	-dump NBR_CYCLES, -dump32 NBR_CYCLES
	-dump64 NBR_CYCLES
		Dump the memory after NBR_CYCLES and quit the game
		(32 or 64 bytes per line).

	-n ID
		Set the id of the following champion to ID (1..4).

	NAME.cor
		File with a champion's bytecode (up to 4 champions in one battle).

	//-t	: listen to the tune
	//-l	: system leaks
	//-?	: enable visualization
	//-d	: different levels of detalisation
